            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Travel back in time at Cumberland Heritage Village Museum and immerse yourself in the daily life of a rural 1920s and 30s community. There’s so much to see and do! Participate in village life as costumed interpreters go about their tasks—you may even be asked to lend a hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Activities and demonstrations are offered Wednesday to Sunday, excluding special event days, between 10 am and 3 pm.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Chat with the merchant at the General Store. Get a glimpse of domestic life as you move between Duford house and Foubert house. Check out a trade demonstration highlighting authentic tools and techniques of the era at the blacksmith forge, sawmill, or print, carpentry and leather smith shops (demonstrations may vary daily). See an authentic 1927 firetruck in the Fire Hall, take quiet moment in Knox Church, and enter the automobile era at Watson’s Garage. Don’t forget to say hello to the heritage breed farm animals who call the museum home each summer.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Pack a lunch and enjoy a picnic on the village green or grab a snack at the canteen.&nbsp;&nbsp;Visit the boutique to discover handmade souvenirs crafted with care by the museum’s tradespeople.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h3><span>Scheduled Activities&nbsp;</span></h3>
<p>Scheduled activities are offered Wednesday to Sunday, excluding special event days.&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Tractor-pulled wagon ride -&nbsp;<strong>10:30 am and 1:30 pm&nbsp;</strong></h4>
<p>Enjoy a tour of the village in our tractor-pulled accessible wagon. &nbsp;</p>
<h4><span>School experiences</span></h4>
<p>Become a student in our one-room schoolhouse and experience how life in the classroom has changed over the past 100 years. Families with kids and adults of all ages are encouraged to take part in these activities together. Visitors are welcome to participate in a single activity or return throughout their visit to experience the full school day. &nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Find your seat – 11 am</strong>&nbsp;<br>
Get in character as a student and interact with the teacher as they make sure everyone is settled in the best place for a day of learning.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Class in session – 11:30 am</strong>&nbsp;<br>
Experience a lesson inspired by early 20<sup>th</sup> century curriculum. Complete recitation and seat work.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Making the grade – 2 pm</strong>&nbsp;<br>
Try your hand at exam questions pulled from an era-appropriate Ontario Teachers’ Manual to see if you are ready to move on to the next Form.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>*Schedule subject to change without notice. Activities and demonstrations, including wagon rides and farm tours, may be adjusted or cancelled in the event of unsafe weather conditions or other unforeseen circumstances. Thank you for your understanding. &nbsp;</strong></p>
</div>
      
