Ages 16 and up<br>
Cost: $102.95 + tax (per person)<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search?locale=en-US&amp;activity_select_param=2&amp;activity_keyword=tinsmithing&amp;viewMode=list">Advance registration is required.&nbsp;</a></p>
<p>Step into the world of tinsmithing, where technical tradition meets creativity in a hands-on exploration of metal craftmanship. In this beginner-friendly workshop, you will work with tin and other metals to cut, shape and assemble a container. You will gain confidence using tools of the trade, including hammers, tin snips, and punches, as you express your unique style. Program supplies are included in the cost of registration. Light refreshments will be served.</p>
